o). This gives adequate coverage of the field, but the essays also help break down the confinement of such categories. The concluding essay looks at the data presented in the book in the framework of contemporary anthropological theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aBauer, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLilley, Rozanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiles, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRajah, Ananda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSatyawadhna, Cholthira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTapp, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWijeyewardene, Gehan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWijeyewardene, Gehan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Archive eBook-Package 1970-1999z978311060669040uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981437936640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814379366423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814379366.jpg  a978-3-11-060669-0  ISEAS Archive eBook-Package 1970-1999c1970d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK